1
00:00:14,222 --> 00:00:15,850
REED: YOU HAVE
A 10-SECOND FIRING WINDOW.

2
00:00:15,891 --> 00:00:17,977
READY?

3
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:20,855
READY.

4
00:00:20,896 --> 00:00:22,397
GO.

5
00:00:30,823 --> 00:00:33,868
TIME.

6
00:00:33,909 --> 00:00:36,119
ANY BETTER?

7
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:39,164
YOUR HIT-TO-MISS RATIO
IS STILL BELOW 50%.

8
00:00:39,206 --> 00:00:41,000
IF THOSE HAD
BEEN LIVE ROUNDS,

9
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:43,544
YOU'D HAVE BLOWN OUT
TWO OR THREE BULKHEADS.

10
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:47,130
I NEVER HAD THIS MUCH TROUBLE
WITH THE EM-33.

11
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:51,343
THIS IS AN ENTIRELY NEW WEAPON.

12
00:00:51,385 --> 00:00:53,637
UNLIKE THE EM-33,

13
00:00:53,679 --> 00:00:56,139
YOU DON'T HAVE TO COMPENSATE
FOR PARTICLE DRIFT.

14
00:00:56,181 --> 00:01:00,310
JUST POINT STRAIGHT
AT THE TARGET.

15
00:01:00,352 --> 00:01:02,855
AND TRY AND KEEP
YOUR SHOULDERS RELAXED.

16
00:01:02,897 --> 00:01:05,900
IT'S HARD TO AIM ACCURATELY
WHEN YOU'RE TENSE.

17
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:06,901
[ SIGHS ]

18
00:01:06,942 --> 00:01:09,110
[ COUGHS ]

19
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:10,905
YOU ALL RIGHT?

20
00:01:10,946 --> 00:01:12,072
YEAH, FINE.

21
00:01:12,113 --> 00:01:13,741
YOU'LL GET THE HANG OF IT.

22
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:16,159
LET'S TRY FOR 20 SECONDS
THIS TIME.

23
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:20,247
[ ENGINES WHOOSH ]

24
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:23,709
I THOUGHT WE WERE STAYING
AT WARP FOR THE NEXT FEW DAYS.

25
00:01:23,751 --> 00:01:27,922
OH, WE'RE APPROACHING
A GAS GIANT -- CLASS-9.

26
00:01:27,963 --> 00:01:31,050
SO MUCH FOR TARGET PRACTICE.

27
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:32,968
WE'LL PICK IT UP TOMORROW.

28
00:01:37,890 --> 00:01:41,977
MAN: ♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

29
00:01:42,019 --> 00:01:45,272
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

30
00:01:45,313 --> 00:01:49,109
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

31
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:53,488
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

32
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:57,158
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

33
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:00,788
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

34
00:02:00,829 --> 00:02:04,792
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

35
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:07,795
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

36
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:10,965
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

37
00:02:11,006 --> 00:02:12,633
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

38
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:16,261
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

39
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:21,100
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

40
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:23,477
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

41
00:02:23,518 --> 00:02:28,356
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

42
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:31,192
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

43
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:36,865
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

44
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:38,784
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

45
00:02:38,826 --> 00:02:41,161
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

46
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:44,957
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

47
00:02:44,999 --> 00:02:49,544
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

48
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:10,983
THE PROBE'S ENTERED
THE OUTER ATMOSPHERE.

49
00:03:11,025 --> 00:03:12,985
ARCHER: CAN WE CLEAN UP
THE SIGNAL?

50
00:03:13,027 --> 00:03:14,945
HOSHI: I'M TRYING, SIR.

51
00:03:14,987 --> 00:03:17,156
THERE'S A LOT
OF E.M. INTERFERENCE

52
00:03:17,196 --> 00:03:20,951
THAT SOUNDS VERY STRANGE.

53
00:03:20,993 --> 00:03:26,874
T'POL: INTENSE MAGNETIC FIELDS
OFTEN CREATE UNIQUE WAVEFORMS.

54
00:03:26,915 --> 00:03:28,876
ARCHER: LET'S HEAR THEM.

55
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:34,173
[<i> HOWLING</i> ]

56
00:03:34,213 --> 00:03:37,718
TRAVIS: SIREN CALLS.

57
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:40,387
THAT'S WHAT WE CALLED THEM
WHEN I WAS A KID.

58
00:03:40,428 --> 00:03:42,097
MY DAD WOULD PUT THEM
THROUGH THE SPEAKERS

59
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:45,350
WHENEVER WE FLEW BY
A GAS GIANT.

60
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:48,187
IT GAVE ME NIGHTMARES SOMETIMES.

61
00:03:50,064 --> 00:03:52,315
T'POL: OTHER THAN KEEPING
ENSIGN MAYWEATHER UP AT NIGHT,

62
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:55,694
I'M NOT SURE WHAT WE EXPECT
TO ACCOMPLISH HERE.

63
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:58,363
THERE ARE FOUR GAS GIANTS
IN YOUR OWN SOLAR SYSTEM.

64
00:03:58,405 --> 00:04:00,741
ARCHER: NONE OF THEM
ARE CLASS-9.

65
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:03,035
I THINK THIS ONE'S
WORTH A CLOSER LOOK.

66
00:04:03,077 --> 00:04:05,162
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

67
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:10,291
I'M READING AN ANOMALOUS
POWER SIGNATURE

68
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:13,128
IN THE LOWER ATMOSPHERE...

69
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:15,380
AND SEVERAL BIO-SIGNS.

70
00:04:17,925 --> 00:04:21,511
ARCHER: GET THE PROBE CLOSER.
TRAVIS: AYE, SIR.

71
00:04:27,768 --> 00:04:29,895
[ SNEEZES ]

72
00:04:29,937 --> 00:04:33,065
WE CAN TRAVEL FASTER
THAN THE SPEED OF LIGHT.

73
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:35,567
YOU'D THINK WE COULD FIND
A CURE FOR THE COMMON COLD.

74
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:38,779
PHLOX: YOU SHOULD BE GRATEFUL
A HUMAN COLD IS SO MILD.

75
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:42,991
I ONCE HAD A PATIENT
WITH THE KAMARAAZITE FLU.

76
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,618
HE SNEEZED SO VIOLENTLY,

77
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:48,038
HE NEARLY REGURGITATED
HIS PINEAL GLAND.

78
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:51,374
I DON'T SEE HOW I COULD
ACTUALLY CATCH A COLD

79
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:53,835
ON A HERMETICALLY SEALED
STARSHIP.

80
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:55,796
OH, YOU MAY HAVE
PICKED UP A VIRUS

81
00:04:55,837 --> 00:04:57,380
FROM A PIECE OF EQUIPMENT.

82
00:04:57,422 --> 00:05:00,341
IT COULD HAVE BEEN LURKING
INSIDE A SEALED CONTAINER.

83
00:05:00,383 --> 00:05:02,136
I DID OPEN A CASE
OF PLASMA COOLANT.

84
00:05:02,177 --> 00:05:06,556
WELL, WHOEVER PACKED THAT CASE
WAS PROBABLY NURSING A COLD.

85
00:05:06,598 --> 00:05:10,644
BUT THAT WAS BACK AT SPACEDOCK
FIVE MONTHS AGO.

86
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:13,772
YOU UNDERESTIMATE THE TENACITY
OF A VIRUS, LIEUTENANT.

87
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:15,690
IT CAN LAY DORMANT FOR MONTHS,

88
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:19,278
ADAPT TO WHATEVER ENVIRONMENT
IT FINDS ITSELF IN, HMM?

89
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,822
THIS SHOULD EASE THE SYMPTOMS.

90
00:05:21,863 --> 00:05:27,119
BUT THE ONLY CURE I KNOW OF
INVOLVES BED REST.

91
00:05:27,161 --> 00:05:29,121
OH, NO, THAT'LL HAVE TO WAIT.

92
00:05:29,163 --> 00:05:32,666
THE CAPTAIN WANTS ME ON THE TEAM
INVESTIGATING THAT SHIPWRECK.

93
00:05:32,707 --> 00:05:34,293
AH.

94
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,211
WELL, YOU WON'T BE CONTAGIOUS
INSIDE AN ENVIRONMENT SUIT.

95
00:05:36,253 --> 00:05:39,965
JUST TRY NOT TO SNEEZE
IN YOUR HELMET.

96
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:41,133
[ SIGHS ]

97
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:43,426
I'LL DO MY BEST.

98
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:49,808
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

99
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:51,434
COME IN.

100
00:05:53,228 --> 00:05:54,395
HOSHI.

101
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:56,231
DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE, SIR?

102
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:58,275
OF COURSE.
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

103
00:05:58,317 --> 00:05:59,484
THAT SHIPWRECK.

104
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:02,445
WE HAVE NO IDEA WHAT TYPE
OF LIFE-FORMS

105
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:05,115
WE'LL FIND
ON THAT ALIEN VESSEL,

106
00:06:05,157 --> 00:06:07,117
AND THERE'S A LOT OF
INTERFERENCE IN THE ATMOSPHERE.

107
00:06:07,159 --> 00:06:10,662
ARE YOU SURE THE AWAY TEAM
WON'T NEED A TRANSLATOR?

108
00:06:10,704 --> 00:06:13,832
ARCHER: THEY HAVE THEIR U.T.s.

109
00:06:13,874 --> 00:06:16,001
AND WE'LL TRY TO KEEP
AN OPEN COM LINK.

110
00:06:16,043 --> 00:06:19,629
WHAT ABOUT THE LANGUAGE ON THE
CONTROL PANELS, THE HATCHES?

111
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:22,841
THEY MIGHT NEED SOMEONE TO HELP
THEM FIND THEIR WAY AROUND.

112
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:27,012
ARE YOU TRYING TO
TELL ME SOMETHING?

113
00:06:27,054 --> 00:06:29,056
I REALIZE THAT
I HAVEN'T ALWAYS BEEN

114
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:33,352
THE FIRST ONE IN LINE
TO VOLUNTEER

115
00:06:33,392 --> 00:06:35,187
FOR THIS TYPE OF MISSION,

116
00:06:35,229 --> 00:06:38,899
BUT I WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT I AM PREPARED TO GO.

117
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:42,610
TOOK A WHILE, BUT I THINK
I FINALLY GOT MY SPACE LEGS.

118
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:45,239
I NEVER DOUBTED
THAT YOU'D FIND THEM.

119
00:06:46,907 --> 00:06:50,660
YOUR TIMING COULDN'T BE BETTER.

120
00:06:50,702 --> 00:06:53,788
T'POL JUST ASKED ME
TO ASSIGN YOU TO THE TEAM.

121
00:06:54,873 --> 00:06:56,624
YOU'D BETTER GET
TO THE LAUNCH BAY

122
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,293
BEFORE THEY LEAVE WITHOUT YOU.

123
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:00,087
AYE, SIR.

124
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:13,558
T'POL: I THOUGHT YOU WERE
ACQUAINTED WITH THE
ENVIRONMENTAL SUIT.

125
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,893
HOSHI: I AM.

126
00:07:14,935 --> 00:07:16,937
I'M JUST BRUSHING UP
ON THE BACKUP SYSTEMS.

127
00:07:16,978 --> 00:07:19,189
I WOULDN'T WANT THE
EMERGENCY OXYGEN TO FAIL

128
00:07:19,231 --> 00:07:20,274
DURING A HULL BREACH.

129
00:07:20,315 --> 00:07:21,858
REED: TRUST ME, ENSIGN.

130
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,735
IF THERE'S A HULL BREACH,
THE PRESSURE WILL CRUSH YOU

131
00:07:23,777 --> 00:07:26,780
INTO SOMETHING
ABOUT THIS BIG.

132
00:07:29,616 --> 00:07:32,493
T'POL: I REQUESTED YOU FOR YOUR
SKILLS AS A TRANSLATOR,

133
00:07:32,535 --> 00:07:33,912
BUT IF YOU'RE UNCOMFORTABLE --

134
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:36,957
I'M PERFECTLY COMFORTABLE.

135
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:41,753
I USED TO FIND THE SUITS
A LITTLE CLAUSTROPHOBIC,

136
00:07:41,795 --> 00:07:44,256
BUT I'M GETTING USED TO THEM.

137
00:07:44,298 --> 00:07:46,758
I'LL SEE YOU IN THE SHUTTLEPOD.

138
00:07:56,726 --> 00:08:00,897
IT'S 100 KILOMETERS BELOW US.
STILL DESCENDING.

139
00:08:00,939 --> 00:08:03,733
GRAVITY'S PULLING IT
DEEPER INTO THE ATMOSPHERE.

140
00:08:03,775 --> 00:08:08,655
AT THEIR CURRENT ALTITUDE,
THE PRESSURE IS 15,000 GSC.

141
00:08:08,696 --> 00:08:12,284
WELL, THAT'S WELL WITHIN
OUR HULL TOLERANCE.

142
00:08:12,326 --> 00:08:13,910
T'POL: FOR THE MOMENT,

143
00:08:13,952 --> 00:08:16,288
BUT AT THE RATE
THAT VESSEL IS SINKING,

144
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:17,705
WE'LL HAVE AN HOUR AT MOST.

145
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:20,750
YOU SOUND UNCOMFORTABLE,
SUBCOMMANDER.

146
00:08:20,792 --> 00:08:22,627
I'M MERELY STATING FACTS.

147
00:08:22,669 --> 00:08:26,006
REED: WE'LL BE ON OUR WAY BACK
WELL BEFORE WE'RE IN ANY DANGER.

148
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:27,299
I, FOR ONE, HAVE NO INTEREST

149
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:29,343
IN IMPLODING
A VALUABLE SHUTTLEPOD.

150
00:08:29,384 --> 00:08:31,761
OR THREE VALUABLE OFFICERS.

151
00:08:31,803 --> 00:08:34,014
[ RUMBLING, ALARM BEEPS ]

152
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:37,434
WE'VE ENTERED
AN EDDY OF LIQUID HELIUM.

153
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:45,317
WE'RE CLEAR.

154
00:08:45,359 --> 00:08:47,652
THAT WASN'T SO BAD.

155
00:08:53,408 --> 00:08:54,826
100 METERS.

156
00:08:54,868 --> 00:08:57,412
IS THAT A HATCH
ON THE PORT SIDE?

157
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:00,290
I SEE IT.

158
00:09:00,332 --> 00:09:01,833
50 METERS.

159
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:04,378
T'POL: 40.

160
00:09:04,419 --> 00:09:06,421
[ ALARM BEEPS ]

161
00:09:06,463 --> 00:09:07,714
WHAT'S THAT?

162
00:09:07,755 --> 00:09:09,257
IT'S JUST A PROXIMITY ALARM.

163
00:09:09,299 --> 00:09:10,842
20 METERS.

164
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:12,927
T'POL: 10.

165
00:09:14,471 --> 00:09:16,681
[RUMBLING]

166
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:19,351
ENGAGING DOCKING INTERFACE.

167
00:09:28,402 --> 00:09:30,320
NITROGEN-OXYGEN ATMOSPHERE.

168
00:09:30,362 --> 00:09:35,616
CARBON-DIOXIDE LEVELS ARE HIGH,
BUT NOTHING'S TOXIC.

169
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:37,118
IT'S BREATHABLE.

170
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,703
YOU FIRST.

171
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:52,926
[ SNIFFS ]

172
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:55,053
PERHAPS WE SHOULD LEAVE
THE HELMETS ON.

173
00:09:55,095 --> 00:09:57,389
-WHAT IS IT?
-[ COUGHS ]

174
00:09:57,431 --> 00:09:58,806
YOU CAN'T SMELL THAT?

175
00:09:58,848 --> 00:10:01,476
NO. THIS DAMN COLD.

176
00:10:01,518 --> 00:10:03,311
COUNT YOUR BLESSINGS.

177
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:16,950
YOU TWO MIGHT WANT TO TAKE
A LOOK AT THIS.

178
00:10:16,991 --> 00:10:19,160
IT SAYS "DECK TWO, RED SECTOR."

179
00:10:19,202 --> 00:10:21,037
WHAT LANGUAGE?

180
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:24,791
KLINGON.

181
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:30,046
HOSHI: I THOUGHT
YOU KNEW KLINGON SHIPS.

182
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:32,840
WHY DIDN'T YOU RECOGNIZE
THIS ONE FROM THE OUTSIDE?

183
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:35,051
T'POL: THERE ARE MANY
CLASSES OF SHIPS.

184
00:10:35,093 --> 00:10:37,262
I'M NOT FAMILIAR
WITH ALL OF THEM.

185
00:10:37,304 --> 00:10:40,348
REED: SO, I'M ASSUMING
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW MANY
KLINGONS ARE ONBOARD.

186
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:44,769
T'POL: I'M READING THREE BIO-
SIGNS, THAT WAY, ALL VERY WEAK.

187
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:47,272
HOSHI: HOW WEAK?

188
00:11:17,636 --> 00:11:20,096
T'POL: THEY'RE STILL ALIVE.

189
00:11:20,138 --> 00:11:23,391
WE SHOULD LEAVE BEFORE THEY
REGAIN CONSCIOUSNESS.

190
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:24,725
AND WHAT IF THEY DON'T?

191
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:26,353
THE ATMOSPHERE IS GOING
TO CRUSH THEIR SHIP

192
00:11:26,394 --> 00:11:27,479
LIKE AN EGGSHELL PRETTY SOON.

193
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:29,481
SHOULDN'T WE TRY TO HELP THEM?

194
00:11:29,523 --> 00:11:30,607
THEY DON'T WANT OUR HELP.

195
00:11:30,649 --> 00:11:31,941
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

196
00:11:31,983 --> 00:11:33,610
THEY'RE KLINGONS.

197
00:11:33,652 --> 00:11:36,904
TO DIE AT THEIR POST ASSURES
THEM A PATH TO THE AFTERLIFE.

198
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:39,449
IF WE RESCUE THEM,
THEY'D BE DISHONORED.

199
00:11:39,491 --> 00:11:41,368
REED: WELL, I, FOR ONE,
DON'T INTEND

200
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:43,702
TO JUST FLY OFF
AND LET THESE PEOPLE DIE,

201
00:11:43,744 --> 00:11:45,079
HONORABLE DEATHS OR NOT.

202
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:48,583
YOUR COMPASSION IS ADMIRABLE,
BUT MISGUIDED.

203
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:53,588
IF THEY AWAKE AND FIND US
ON THEIR SHIP, THEY'LL KILL US.

204
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:20,574
Archer: How many are there?

205
00:12:20,615 --> 00:12:22,242
T'POL: THREE ON THE BRIDGE.

206
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:25,953
BUT I'M DETECTING AT LEAST
NINE MORE BIO-SIGNS ONBOARD.

207
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,997
Archer: You can't tell
what happened to them?

208
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:29,583
I'M DETECTING RESIDUAL AMOUNTS

209
00:12:29,624 --> 00:12:32,586
of a carbon-dioxide-based
neurotoxin,

210
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:34,546
but it seems to have dissipated.

211
00:12:34,588 --> 00:12:36,339
There's not enough to affect us.

212
00:12:36,381 --> 00:12:37,674
STAND BY.

213
00:12:37,716 --> 00:12:40,968
HOW LONG IS THE POD'S HULL
GOING TO HOLD UP?

214
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:43,597
AT THEIR PRESENT RATE
OF DESCENT...

215
00:12:43,638 --> 00:12:45,973
HALF-HOUR, GIVE OR TAKE.

216
00:12:49,644 --> 00:12:51,020
T'POL.

217
00:12:51,062 --> 00:12:52,564
T'Pol: Yes, Captain.

218
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:53,898
YOU'VE GOT 20 MINUTES

219
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:55,900
TO SEE IF YOU CAN DO ANYTHING
FOR THAT CREW.

220
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:57,444
THEN I WANT YOU OUT OF THERE.

221
00:12:57,485 --> 00:12:59,112
Archer: Understood?

222
00:12:59,153 --> 00:13:01,489
I DON'T BELIEVE THERE'S ANYTHING
WE CAN DO IN 20 MINUTES.

223
00:13:01,531 --> 00:13:02,781
I SUGGEST WE LEAVE NOW.

224
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:04,200
Archer: You have
a margin of safety...

225
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:06,453
[ Static ]

226
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:08,371
CAPTAIN?

227
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:13,334
T'POL TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

228
00:13:13,376 --> 00:13:14,586
[ Static ]

229
00:13:14,628 --> 00:13:16,379
REED: DAMN INTERFERENCE.

230
00:13:16,421 --> 00:13:18,131
T'POL: OR WE'VE DROPPED
OUT OF COM RANGE.

231
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:19,716
HOSHI: WE STILL HAVE 20 MINUTES.

232
00:13:19,758 --> 00:13:21,426
T'POL: IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE
TO PLACE OURSELVES AT RISK

233
00:13:21,468 --> 00:13:22,677
WHEN THEY'D RATHER DIE.

234
00:13:22,719 --> 00:13:24,178
REED: THERE MUST BE
SOMETHING WE CAN DO.

235
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,514
MAYBE THEY HAVE A DISTRESS
BEACON WE CAN ACTIVATE.

236
00:13:26,556 --> 00:13:28,057
T'POL: I DOUBT YOU'LL FIND ONE.

237
00:13:28,099 --> 00:13:29,768
KLINGONS DON'T CALL FOR HELP.

238
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:31,728
HOSHI: WHAT IF WE CARRY SOME
OF THEM INTO THE POD?

239
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:34,522
WE COULD SAVE THREE OR FOUR.

240
00:13:34,564 --> 00:13:37,024
AND IF THEY WAKE UP ON THE TRIP
BACK TO<i> ENTERPRISE?</i>

241
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:38,401
[ DOOR OPENS ]

242
00:13:56,711 --> 00:13:57,671
AAH!

243
00:13:57,712 --> 00:13:59,005
UGH!

244
00:14:14,312 --> 00:14:16,606
OHH.

245
00:14:16,648 --> 00:14:17,691
[ ENGINES WHOOSH ]

246
00:14:17,732 --> 00:14:18,692
[ BEEP ]

247
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:20,026
WHAT'S THAT?

248
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,487
IT'S OUR SHUTTLEPOD TAKING OFF.

249
00:14:34,499 --> 00:14:36,125
TRY IT NOW.

250
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:40,254
ARCHER TO T'POL.

251
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,340
WHAT'S YOUR STATUS?

252
00:14:42,382 --> 00:14:45,760
[ Static ]

253
00:14:45,802 --> 00:14:47,721
THEY'RE BACK IN COM RANGE.

254
00:14:47,762 --> 00:14:51,599
TRAVIS: CAPTAIN.

255
00:14:51,641 --> 00:14:53,810
SHUTTLEPOD 1, RESPOND.

256
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:59,065
SIR, THEY'RE HEADING
INTO OPEN SPACE.

257
00:15:01,275 --> 00:15:04,654
TRIP: I'M PICKING UP SOMETHING.

258
00:15:04,696 --> 00:15:06,740
[<i> SPEAKING KLINGON</i> ]

259
00:15:09,116 --> 00:15:11,077
SOUNDS LIKE KLINGON.

260
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:13,830
I'LL TRY TO TIE IN THE U.T.

261
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:20,253
KLINGON:<i> ...IN RANGE. RESPOND.</i>

262
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:22,338
<i>WE'VE BEEN ATTACKED</i>
<i>BY AN UNKNOWN SHIP,</i>

263
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:25,007
<i>DESIGNATION</i> ENTERPRISE NX-01.

264
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:27,927
ANY WARSHIPS IN RANGE, RESPOND.

265
00:15:27,968 --> 00:15:29,763
ARCHER: SET A PURSUIT COURSE.

266
00:15:29,804 --> 00:15:31,972
TRAVIS: AYE, SIR.

267
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:33,974
BRING THE GRAPPLER ONLINE.

268
00:15:45,236 --> 00:15:47,947
TRIP: WE'VE GOT IT.

269
00:15:47,988 --> 00:15:49,824
BRIDGE TO SECURITY.

270
00:15:49,866 --> 00:15:51,451
SEND A TEAM TO LAUNCH BAY 1.

271
00:15:51,492 --> 00:15:53,787
TRIP.
THE BRIDGE IS YOURS, TRAVIS.

272
00:15:53,828 --> 00:15:55,705
TRAVIS: YES, SIR.

273
00:16:22,022 --> 00:16:23,817
[ GRUNTING ]

274
00:16:34,869 --> 00:16:36,454
EVERYBODY ALL RIGHT?

275
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:45,630
ARCHER TO THE BRIDGE.

276
00:16:45,672 --> 00:16:47,006
Travis: Mayweather.

277
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:49,509
HAVE YOU STILL
GOT A FIX ON THE SHIPWRECK?

278
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:50,927
Travis: Yes, sir.

279
00:16:50,969 --> 00:16:53,554
TRANSFER THE COORDINATES
TO THE LAUNCH BAY.

280
00:16:53,596 --> 00:16:55,682
I'M GOING BACK
FOR THE BOARDING PARTY.

281
00:16:55,723 --> 00:16:58,643
Travis: Sir, the alien ship
sunk another 2,000 meters.

282
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:01,354
It's below
the shuttle's safety limits.

283
00:17:03,898 --> 00:17:06,776
THEN POLARIZE THE HULL PLATING.

284
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:09,195
WE'LL TAKE<i> ENTERPRISE</i> DOWN.

285
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:11,906
REED: THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOME WAY OFF THIS SHIP.

286
00:17:11,948 --> 00:17:13,658
HOSHI: WHAT ABOUT ESCAPE PODS?

287
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,117
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT
THE STRUCTURAL INTEGRITY

288
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:16,577
OF KLINGON ESCAPE PODS.

289
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:18,245
MY GUESS IS WE'RE
BETTER OFF IN HERE.

290
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:20,331
T'POL: IT'S IRRELEVANT,
LIEUTENANT.

291
00:17:20,373 --> 00:17:22,542
KLINGONS DON'T USE ESCAPE PODS.

292
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:25,795
IT WOULD BE CONSIDERED
AN ACT OF COWARDICE

293
00:17:25,837 --> 00:17:27,129
TO ABANDON SHIP.

294
00:17:27,171 --> 00:17:28,589
HOSHI: MAYBE WE CAN USE
THEIR COM SYSTEM

295
00:17:28,631 --> 00:17:30,174
TO CONTACT<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

296
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:32,552
T'POL: I DOUBT THEIR COM
WILL PENETRATE THE E.M. FIELD

297
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:33,845
ANY BETTER THAN OUR OWN.

298
00:17:33,887 --> 00:17:35,889
IF WE CAN ACCESS
THEIR HELM CONTROLS,

299
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:38,391
WE MIGHT BE ABLE TO PUT THIS
VESSEL INTO A STABLE ORBIT.

300
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:41,895
REED: I HAVEN'T HAD MUCH
EXPERIENCE AT PILOTING
KLINGON SHIPS.

301
00:17:41,936 --> 00:17:43,563
WE HAVE NO OTHER CHOICE.

302
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:48,526
[ RUMBLING, CREAKING ]

303
00:17:48,568 --> 00:17:51,029
START TRANSLATING
THOSE CONSOLES.

304
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,114
LOOK FOR ANYTHING MARKED
PROPULSION, HELM, NAVIGATION.

305
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:55,533
I'LL TRY, BUT READING KLINGON

306
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:57,618
IS A LOT DIFFERENT
THAN SPEAKING IT.

307
00:17:57,660 --> 00:18:01,163
WE COULD ALWAYS TRY WAKING
ONE OF THEM TO HELP US.

308
00:18:01,205 --> 00:18:02,790
ALL RIGHT.

309
00:18:09,296 --> 00:18:11,758
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

310
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:15,595
"PLASMA CONTAINMENT," MAYBE?

311
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:18,180
T'POL: YOU'RE CERTAIN?

312
00:18:18,222 --> 00:18:21,183
HOSHI: "CONTAINMENT."

313
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:22,894
I'M CERTAIN.

314
00:18:31,652 --> 00:18:33,947
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

315
00:18:33,988 --> 00:18:37,617
SOMETHING THEY CALL
PHOTON TORPEDOES?

316
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:38,993
REED: PHOTON TORPEDOES?

317
00:18:39,035 --> 00:18:41,370
I NEVER HEARD OF ANYTHING
LIKE THAT. WHAT ELSE?

318
00:18:41,412 --> 00:18:43,664
THIS ALL LOOKS
LIKE WEAPONS SYSTEMS --

319
00:18:43,706 --> 00:18:47,209
TORPEDOES, TACTICAL SENSORS,
DISRUPTOR ARRAYS.

320
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:49,087
WHAT ABOUT THIS ONE?

321
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:56,218
HOSHI: I RECOGNIZE
"PRESSURE."

322
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:57,344
[ SPEAKS KLINGON ]

323
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:59,973
THAT CAN MEAN
"WALL" OR "BARRIER."

324
00:19:00,014 --> 00:19:01,515
T'POL: OR "HULL"?

325
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:03,434
HOSHI: MAYBE.

326
00:19:03,476 --> 00:19:06,687
REED: IF I'M READING THIS
CORRECTLY, WE'VE GOT
A FEW HOURS AT MOST.

327
00:19:06,729 --> 00:19:08,689
THE HULL INTEGRITY
IS FAILING.

328
00:19:08,731 --> 00:19:10,566
T'POL: THEN WE BETTER HURRY.

329
00:19:10,608 --> 00:19:13,527
THIS APPEARS
TO BE THE HELM STATION.

330
00:19:13,569 --> 00:19:15,195
HOSHI: I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

331
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:17,406
[ SPEAKS KLINGON ]
"IMPULSE DRIVE."

332
00:19:17,448 --> 00:19:18,908
REED: GOOD WORK, HOSHI.

333
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:26,499
[ BEEPING ]

334
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:28,709
[ ALARM BLARING ]

335
00:19:28,751 --> 00:19:29,919
REED: HOSHI?

336
00:19:29,961 --> 00:19:32,922
HOSHI: IT SAYS THE
PRESSURE'S FAILING

337
00:19:32,964 --> 00:19:34,882
IN THE [SPEAKS KLINGON]
"FUSION MANIFOLD."

338
00:19:34,924 --> 00:19:36,050
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS?

339
00:19:36,092 --> 00:19:38,094
TO QUOTE OUR VERY OWN
MR. TUCKER,

340
00:19:38,136 --> 00:19:40,387
IT MEANS WE'RE
DEAD IN THE WATER.

341
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:42,264
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
Archer: Archer
to boarding party.

342
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:45,267
Come in.

343
00:19:45,309 --> 00:19:46,602
HOSHI: WE READ YOU, CAPTAIN.

344
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:48,479
HOW ARE YOU HOLDING UP?

345
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:50,272
Hoshi: We're doing okay, sir.

346
00:19:50,314 --> 00:19:52,232
It's nice to hear your voice.

347
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:53,860
WHAT'S YOUR STATUS?

348
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:56,403
T'POL: WE'VE BEEN ATTEMPTING
TO RESTART THEIR ENGINES,

349
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:58,156
BUT THEY APPEAR
TO BE OFFLINE.

350
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:02,284
Archer: Don't worry about it.
We're coming to get you.

351
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:04,620
TRAVIS, HOW MUCH FARTHER?

352
00:20:04,662 --> 00:20:06,122
10,000 METERS,

353
00:20:06,164 --> 00:20:09,083
BUT I'M HAVING A HARD TIME
GETTING A FIX ON THEM.

354
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:10,835
TOO MUCH INTERFERENCE.

355
00:20:13,129 --> 00:20:16,090
IS OUR PROBE STILL WORKING?

356
00:20:16,132 --> 00:20:17,466
TRIP: BARELY.

357
00:20:17,508 --> 00:20:20,386
TRY USING IT TO TRIANGULATE
THEIR POSITION.

358
00:20:25,975 --> 00:20:27,601
THE PROBE'S GONE.

359
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:29,395
[ CREAKING ]

360
00:20:29,436 --> 00:20:32,272
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

361
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:35,693
SIR, EXTERNAL PRESSURE'S
AT MAXIMUM.

362
00:20:37,403 --> 00:20:39,030
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

363
00:20:39,072 --> 00:20:43,701
I'M AFRAID WE'VE GOT A LITTLE
HITCH IN OUR RESCUE PLAN.

364
00:20:43,743 --> 00:20:46,328
THE HULL PLATING IS FAILING.

365
00:20:49,498 --> 00:20:51,709
WE'LL BE BACK FOR YOU
AS SOON AS WE CAN.

366
00:20:51,751 --> 00:20:53,460
Archer: [ Distorted ] In the
meantime, just sit tight.

367
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:56,255
See what you can do
about getting those
engines back online.

368
00:20:56,296 --> 00:20:59,759
HOSHI: CAPTAIN,
YOU'RE BREAKING UP.

369
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,385
CAPTAIN?

370
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,518
RELEASE ME!

371
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:13,439
COWARDS!
LET ME DIE ON MY FEET!

372
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,815
PHLOX: T'POL WAS RIGHT.

373
00:21:14,857 --> 00:21:17,985
THERE'S A NEUROTOXIN
IN HER BLOODSTREAM.

374
00:21:18,027 --> 00:21:20,863
UNTREATED, IT COULD KILL HER
WITHIN A DAY OR TWO.

375
00:21:20,905 --> 00:21:22,322
ARCHER: CAN YOU DO ANYTHING?

376
00:21:22,364 --> 00:21:23,824
PHLOX: I'M WORKING ON IT.

377
00:21:23,866 --> 00:21:27,327
TRIP: T'POL SAID THE KLINGONS
WERE UNCONSCIOUS.

378
00:21:27,369 --> 00:21:29,163
WHY IS THIS ONE SO LIVELY?

379
00:21:29,205 --> 00:21:31,749
PHLOX: SHE'S SHOWING THE EFFECTS
OF HYPOTHERMIA.

380
00:21:31,791 --> 00:21:33,667
MY GUESS IS SHE TOOK REFUGE

381
00:21:33,709 --> 00:21:36,045
IN A LOW-TEMPERATURE
ENVIRONMENT ABOARD HER SHIP.

382
00:21:36,087 --> 00:21:38,589
THE COLD WOULD HAVE DELAYED
THE EFFECTS OF THE TOXIN.

383
00:21:38,631 --> 00:21:40,883
KLINGON: I DEMAND
TO SPEAK TO YOUR CAPTAIN.

384
00:21:40,925 --> 00:21:43,677
TRIP: YOU KNOW, I READ IF THEY
SENSE A LEADER'S WEAK,

385
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:47,223
THEY'LL TRY TO KILL HIM
AND TAKE COMMAND.

386
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:55,648
I'M THE CAPTAIN.

387
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:58,109
I HAVE NEVER SEEN
YOUR KIND BEFORE,

388
00:21:58,151 --> 00:22:00,987
BUT YOU HAVE MADE AN ENEMY
OF THE KLINGON EMPIRE.

389
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:04,657
FROM WHAT I'VE NOTICED,
THAT'S NOT HARD TO DO.

390
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:07,409
YOU STRANDED THREE
OF MY PEOPLE DOWN THERE.

391
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:10,370
YOU RAIDED MY VESSEL,
INFECTED MY CREW!

392
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:11,705
WE DIDN'T INFECT ANYONE.

393
00:22:11,747 --> 00:22:14,959
WE BOARDED YOUR SHIP
TO TRY AND HELP.

394
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:17,170
LIAR.

395
00:22:17,211 --> 00:22:20,881
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR CREW,

396
00:22:20,923 --> 00:22:23,843
BUT WE HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT.

397
00:22:23,884 --> 00:22:27,345
NOW YOUR VESSEL IS SINKING
DEEPER INTO THE ATMOSPHERE.

398
00:22:27,387 --> 00:22:30,099
UNLESS WE DO SOMETHING,
IT'LL BE DESTROYED.

399
00:22:30,141 --> 00:22:33,978
BETTER THAT THAN LET IT FALL
INTO YOUR HANDS.

400
00:22:35,395 --> 00:22:38,774
I'VE GOT THREE VERY CAPABLE
PEOPLE ON YOUR SHIP.

401
00:22:38,816 --> 00:22:40,151
LET THEM HELP.

402
00:22:40,193 --> 00:22:42,444
IF YOU TELL THEM HOW TO GET
THE ENGINES RUNNING,

403
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:44,613
THEY CAN FLY IT OUT OF THERE.

404
00:22:44,655 --> 00:22:45,865
AND FLY IT WHERE?

405
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:49,451
BACK TO YOUR WORLD
TO STEAL OUR SECRETS?

406
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:51,204
NO.

407
00:22:51,245 --> 00:22:56,458
WHEN OUR BIRDS-OF-PREY ARRIVE,
YOUR SHIP WILL BE DESTROYED.

408
00:23:02,380 --> 00:23:05,134
REMIND ME TO STOP
TRYING TO HELP PEOPLE.

409
00:23:13,059 --> 00:23:15,644
TRAVIS: I FOUND THESE SCHEMATICS
IN THE VULCAN DATABASE.

410
00:23:15,686 --> 00:23:18,064
IT'S A RAPTOR-CLASS
SCOUT VESSEL.

411
00:23:18,105 --> 00:23:20,316
HOW LONG WILL IT
LAST DOWN THERE?

412
00:23:20,358 --> 00:23:23,027
ITS HULL'S AT LEAST
TWICE AS THICK AS OURS,

413
00:23:23,069 --> 00:23:26,446
REINFORCED WITH SOME KIND
OF COHERENT MOLECULAR ALLOY.

414
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:28,199
YEAH, IT'S
A TOUGH LITTLE SHIP,

415
00:23:28,241 --> 00:23:31,744
BUT IT CAN'T HOLD UP
UNDER THAT PRESSURE FOREVER.

416
00:23:36,082 --> 00:23:37,624
WHAT IF WE USE
DURATANIUM BRACES

417
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:39,126
TO REINFORCE A SHUTTLEPOD?

418
00:23:39,168 --> 00:23:40,878
IT WON'T LOOK PRETTY, BUT...

419
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:44,215
IT MIGHT HOLD UP LONG ENOUGH
FOR US TO GET OUR PEOPLE OUT.

420
00:23:44,257 --> 00:23:47,009
OUR ONLY OTHER OPTION
IS FOR T'POL AND MALCOLM

421
00:23:47,051 --> 00:23:49,303
TO FIX A BROKEN-DOWN
KLINGON SHIP

422
00:23:49,345 --> 00:23:51,097
AND FLY IT OUT THEMSELVES.

423
00:23:53,431 --> 00:23:55,517
I DON'T THINK WE'RE GONNA
GET ANY HELP

424
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:58,729
FROM OUR GUEST IN SICK BAY.

425
00:23:58,771 --> 00:24:00,314
GET STARTED ON THOSE BRACES.

426
00:24:00,356 --> 00:24:01,607
KEEP AN EYE OUT

427
00:24:01,648 --> 00:24:03,817
FOR ANY KLINGON SHIPS
COMING THIS WAY.

428
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:05,111
AYE, SIR.

429
00:24:07,738 --> 00:24:10,241
AH, THE ONE TIME WE NEED
OUR CHIEF ENGINEER

430
00:24:10,283 --> 00:24:12,743
IS THE ONE TIME
WE LEAVE HIM BEHIND.

431
00:24:12,785 --> 00:24:14,452
COME LOOK AT THIS.

432
00:24:19,499 --> 00:24:21,835
[<i> SPEAKING KLINGON</i> ]

433
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:33,055
<i>...Q'TAHL-CLASS PLANET.</i>

434
00:24:33,097 --> 00:24:38,060
<i>WE DESTROYED THEIR SHIP,</i>
<i>BUT WE'VE SUSTAINED DAMAGE</i>

435
00:24:38,102 --> 00:24:40,396
<i>IN OUR PORT FUSION INJECTOR.</i>

436
00:24:40,438 --> 00:24:43,899
<i>WE'VE DESCENDED</i>
<i>INTO THE OUTER ATMOSPHERE</i>

437
00:24:43,941 --> 00:24:47,320
<i>OF A Q'TAHL-CLASS PLANET</i>
<i>TO MAKE REPAIRS,</i>

438
00:24:47,361 --> 00:24:51,657
<i>IN CASE THERE ARE OTHER</i>
<i>XARANTINE SHIPS IN THE AREA.</i>

439
00:24:51,698 --> 00:24:54,076
[<i> COUGHING</i> ]

440
00:24:57,579 --> 00:24:59,873
<i>MY CREW IS FALLING ILL,</i>

441
00:24:59,915 --> 00:25:02,960
<i>AND I HAVE BEEN UNABLE</i>
<i>TO DETERMINE WHY.</i>

442
00:25:03,002 --> 00:25:06,255
<i>IF WE HAD DIED</i>
<i>WHEN THE XARANTINE ATTACKED,</i>

443
00:25:06,297 --> 00:25:07,923
<i>OUR HONOR WOULD BE SECURE,</i>

444
00:25:07,965 --> 00:25:10,676
<i>BUT TO FALL VICTIM</i>
<i>TO SOME DISEASE,</i>

445
00:25:10,717 --> 00:25:13,471
<i>TO BE CRUSHED INTO NOTHING</i>

446
00:25:13,511 --> 00:25:17,350
<i>IN THE DEPTHS</i>
<i>OF THIS MISERABLE PLANET --</i>

447
00:25:17,391 --> 00:25:19,059
[<i> COUGHING</i> ]

448
00:25:22,438 --> 00:25:25,983
REED: SOUNDS LIKE WE NEED TO
FIND THE PORT FUSION INJECTOR.

449
00:25:26,025 --> 00:25:28,526
WAIT, I SAW THAT SOMEWHERE.

450
00:25:33,657 --> 00:25:35,993
HOSHI: HERE. ONE DECK BELOW US.

451
00:25:36,035 --> 00:25:38,454
IT'S IN THE REACTOR PIT.

452
00:25:38,496 --> 00:25:41,040
REED: REACTOR PIT?
COULD THAT BE ENGINEERING?

453
00:25:41,081 --> 00:25:42,708
HOSHI: COULD BE.

454
00:26:05,689 --> 00:26:06,982
REED: THIS ONE?

455
00:26:07,024 --> 00:26:08,275
HOSHI: NO.

456
00:26:08,317 --> 00:26:11,362
THAT SAYS SOMETHING
ABOUT PLASMA INDUCTION.

457
00:26:19,703 --> 00:26:23,665
HERE IT IS.

458
00:26:23,707 --> 00:26:26,626
"PORT FUSION INJECTOR."

459
00:26:32,716 --> 00:26:34,260
[ BOTH GRUNT ]

460
00:26:38,013 --> 00:26:40,682
ARCHER: I THINK I MIGHT HAVE
MADE A TACTICAL ERROR

461
00:26:40,724 --> 00:26:42,642
DEALING WITH THE KLINGON WOMAN.

462
00:26:42,684 --> 00:26:44,437
I ASKED HER FOR HELP.

463
00:26:44,478 --> 00:26:46,439
SHE COULD SEE THAT
AS A SIGN OF WEAKNESS.

464
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:50,692
TRIP: YOU BEEN BONING UP
ON YOUR KLINGON PSYCHOLOGY?

465
00:26:50,734 --> 00:26:52,610
ARCHER: WE'VE RUN
INTO THEM THREE TIMES,

466
00:26:52,652 --> 00:26:55,655
AND EVERY TIME THEY'VE
WANTED TO DESTROY US.

467
00:26:55,697 --> 00:26:57,615
I'D LOVE TO FIGURE OUT WHY.

468
00:26:57,657 --> 00:27:00,660
TRIP: YOU KNOW, MAYBE
THE BEST THING IS JUST
TO STEER CLEAR OF THEM.

469
00:27:00,702 --> 00:27:02,620
ARCHER: THAT MIGHT
NOT BE SO EASY,

470
00:27:02,662 --> 00:27:06,250
BUT WE COULD USE
THEIR HELP RIGHT NOW.

471
00:27:06,292 --> 00:27:08,294
IF WE COULD REESTABLISH
A COM SIGNAL

472
00:27:08,335 --> 00:27:10,003
WITH T'POL AND THE OTHERS,

473
00:27:10,045 --> 00:27:13,215
THE KLINGON WOMAN COULD PROBABLY
TALK THEM THROUGH THE REPAIRS,

474
00:27:13,257 --> 00:27:15,759
BUT SHE'S GOT A THOUSAND
GENERATIONS OF INSTINCT

475
00:27:15,801 --> 00:27:17,303
TELLING HER NOT TO TRUST ME.

476
00:27:17,344 --> 00:27:18,471
TRIP: WELL, MAYBE IT'S TIME

477
00:27:18,512 --> 00:27:21,223
YOU STARTED THINKING
LIKE A KLINGON.

478
00:27:40,117 --> 00:27:41,952
AAH!

479
00:27:41,994 --> 00:27:43,496
HOSHI: ARE YOU OKAY?

480
00:27:43,537 --> 00:27:44,746
REED: YES!

481
00:27:44,788 --> 00:27:47,082
I SEEM TO BE GETTING
A LITTLE LIGHTHEADED.

482
00:27:47,124 --> 00:27:50,419
MUST BE THE HEAT.

483
00:27:50,461 --> 00:27:53,172
T'POL: YOU'RE DEHYDRATED.
YOU NEED SOME WATER.

484
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:55,549
HOSHI: I SAW A GALLEY
ON THE SCHEMATICS --

485
00:27:55,591 --> 00:27:57,009
DECK FOUR, BLUE SECTOR.

486
00:27:57,050 --> 00:27:58,676
I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN FIND.

487
00:27:58,718 --> 00:28:00,137
T'POL: YOU SHOULDN'T GO ALONE.

488
00:28:02,598 --> 00:28:04,057
WATCH YOURSELVES.

489
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:14,860
UGH.

490
00:28:22,034 --> 00:28:23,701
T'POL: IT'S CALLED GAGH.

491
00:28:23,743 --> 00:28:27,080
IT'S A KLINGON DELICACY,
BUT ONLY WHEN THEY'RE ALIVE.

492
00:28:27,122 --> 00:28:28,790
HOSHI: THEY LOOK LIKE WORMS.

493
00:28:28,832 --> 00:28:30,750
THEY ARE WORMS.

494
00:28:53,899 --> 00:28:55,568
[ GASPS ]

495
00:28:55,609 --> 00:28:59,154
[ RATTLING ]

496
00:29:20,884 --> 00:29:23,554
[ ROARING ]

497
00:29:23,596 --> 00:29:27,807
[ GASPS ]

498
00:29:27,849 --> 00:29:30,060
T'POL: TARGS.

499
00:29:30,102 --> 00:29:33,606
KLINGONS PREFER THEIR FOOD
FRESHLY SLAUGHTERED.

500
00:29:33,647 --> 00:29:37,192
[ PANTING ]

501
00:29:37,234 --> 00:29:39,152
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

502
00:29:39,194 --> 00:29:41,780
HOSHI: I PROMISED MYSELF
I WOULDN'T DO THIS.

503
00:29:41,821 --> 00:29:47,035
YOU'RE IN A DANGEROUS SITUATION
IN AN ALIEN ENVIRONMENT.

504
00:29:47,077 --> 00:29:49,496
YOUR ANXIETY IS UNDERSTANDABLE.

505
00:29:49,538 --> 00:29:51,290
[ SIGHS ]

506
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:53,417
DON'T YOU MEAN "FOR A HUMAN"?

507
00:29:53,459 --> 00:29:56,044
T'POL: YOU CAN'T DENY
YOUR NATURE.

508
00:29:56,086 --> 00:29:58,838
HOSHI: THIS MAY
SOUND STRANGE.

509
00:30:00,924 --> 00:30:02,884
BUT I ENVY YOU SOMETIMES.

510
00:30:02,926 --> 00:30:04,428
I KNOW.

511
00:30:04,470 --> 00:30:08,974
ANOTHER...PESKY HUMAN EMOTION.

512
00:30:10,016 --> 00:30:12,311
BUT THERE ARE TIMES
I WISH I COULD

513
00:30:12,352 --> 00:30:14,896
JUST IGNORE MY FEELINGS,

514
00:30:14,938 --> 00:30:18,358
BURY THEM THE WAY VULCANS DO.

515
00:30:20,902 --> 00:30:22,904
TAKE MY HAND.

516
00:30:22,946 --> 00:30:24,531
EXCUSE ME?

517
00:30:27,743 --> 00:30:30,036
MY HAND.

518
00:30:37,961 --> 00:30:39,963
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

519
00:30:45,678 --> 00:30:49,807
THINK OF YOURSELF
ON A TURBULENT OCEAN.

520
00:30:50,974 --> 00:30:54,561
YOU HAVE THE POWER
TO CONTROL THE WAVES.

521
00:30:57,856 --> 00:31:00,942
WHATEVER IT IS YOU'RE TRYING
TO DO, IT'S NOT WORKING.

522
00:31:00,984 --> 00:31:03,153
FOCUS.

523
00:31:04,446 --> 00:31:07,157
THE WAVES ARE SUBSIDING.

524
00:31:07,199 --> 00:31:10,744
THE WATER IS GROWING STILL.

525
00:31:13,205 --> 00:31:15,541
YOU'RE IN CONTROL.

526
00:31:27,093 --> 00:31:31,181
THAT WAS...AMAZING.

527
00:31:31,223 --> 00:31:33,016
WHEN WE RETURN TO THE SHIP,

528
00:31:33,058 --> 00:31:36,269
I'LL TEACH YOU HOW TO DO IT
ON YOUR OWN.

529
00:31:38,021 --> 00:31:39,981
THANKS.

530
00:31:42,025 --> 00:31:44,069
[ RATTLING ]

531
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:46,112
T'POL: LIEUTENANT REED, REPORT.

532
00:31:46,154 --> 00:31:48,990
REED: THE HULL PRESSURE'S
APPROACHING CRITICAL!

533
00:31:49,032 --> 00:31:51,535
THIS SHIP'S ABOUT TO BE CRUSHED!

534
00:32:02,003 --> 00:32:03,839
IT'LL WORK.

535
00:32:03,881 --> 00:32:07,175
IF YOU'RE WRONG,
IT COULD DESTROY THE SHIP.

536
00:32:07,217 --> 00:32:09,511
[ CREAKING ]

537
00:32:11,805 --> 00:32:13,766
LOOK, EVEN WITH HOSHI'S HELP,

538
00:32:13,807 --> 00:32:16,769
IT COULD TAKE HOURS JUST TO FIND
THE FUSION INJECTOR IN HERE.

539
00:32:16,810 --> 00:32:18,353
WE'RE OUT OF TIME.

540
00:32:18,395 --> 00:32:20,397
I SAY WE TRY THE WEAPONS.

541
00:32:20,439 --> 00:32:22,941
HOW DO YOU KNOW YOU CAN EVEN
ACCESS THE TACTICAL SYSTEMS?

542
00:32:22,982 --> 00:32:24,484
IF THERE'S ONE THING
ONBOARD THIS SHIP

543
00:32:24,526 --> 00:32:27,946
I OUGHT TO BE ABLE TO FIGURE
OUT, IT'S THE TORPEDOES.

544
00:32:27,987 --> 00:32:30,031
TRIP: I'D LIKE TO RUN
ONE MORE STRUCTURAL DIAGNOSTIC

545
00:32:30,073 --> 00:32:32,200
BEFORE YOU LAUNCH.

546
00:32:32,242 --> 00:32:34,870
QAPLA'.

547
00:32:34,912 --> 00:32:36,747
BEG YOUR PARDON?

548
00:32:36,789 --> 00:32:38,373
SUCCESS.

549
00:32:38,415 --> 00:32:41,835
I DECIDED TO TAKE YOUR ADVICE
ABOUT THINKING LIKE A KLINGON.

550
00:32:41,877 --> 00:32:45,088
THE VULCAN DATABASE HAS
ABOUT 900 PAGES ON THEM.

551
00:32:45,130 --> 00:32:46,590
TRIP: LEARN ANYTHING?

552
00:32:46,632 --> 00:32:48,091
PLENTY.

553
00:32:48,133 --> 00:32:50,009
THEY'RE DRIVEN BY
A WARRIOR MENTALITY.

554
00:32:50,051 --> 00:32:53,012
THEY TEND TO VIEW ANYONE
THEY MEET AS A POTENTIAL ENEMY.

555
00:32:53,054 --> 00:32:56,892
THAT MAY EXPLAIN WHY
OUR GUEST IS SO IRRITABLE.

556
00:32:56,934 --> 00:32:59,102
THEY ALSO HAVE
A STRONG SENSE OF DUTY.

557
00:32:59,144 --> 00:33:03,482
UH...
[ SPEAKS KLINGON ]

558
00:33:03,523 --> 00:33:07,986
"DEATH BEFORE DISHONOR."

559
00:33:08,027 --> 00:33:10,363
FINISH UP THAT DIAGNOSTIC.
I'LL BE IN SICK BAY.

560
00:33:10,405 --> 00:33:12,115
GONNA GO PUT
YOUR HOMEWORK TO USE?

561
00:33:12,157 --> 00:33:13,700
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

562
00:33:23,126 --> 00:33:24,461
PHLOX: PLEASE RELAX.

563
00:33:24,503 --> 00:33:26,338
IF YOU STRAIN
AGAINST THE STRAPS,

564
00:33:26,379 --> 00:33:27,923
YOU MIGHT HURT YOURSELF.

565
00:33:27,965 --> 00:33:29,341
WHAT'S THAT?

566
00:33:29,382 --> 00:33:31,343
IS THAT WHAT YOU USED
AGAINST MY CREW?

567
00:33:31,384 --> 00:33:33,720
DR. PHLOX HAS DEVELOPED
AN ANTIDOTE

568
00:33:33,762 --> 00:33:35,889
TO THE NEUROTOXIN
IN YOUR SYSTEM.

569
00:33:35,931 --> 00:33:39,225
IS THIS HOW YOU PLAN
TO GAIN MY TRUST?

570
00:33:39,267 --> 00:33:43,856
FIRST POISON ME,
THEN MIRACULOUSLY CURE ME?

571
00:33:45,398 --> 00:33:47,776
HAVE YOU HAD A DRINK LATELY?

572
00:33:47,818 --> 00:33:49,027
WHAT?

573
00:33:49,068 --> 00:33:50,487
ARCHER: THE BIO-AGENT

574
00:33:50,529 --> 00:33:53,072
THAT AFFECTED YOU AND YOUR CREW
WAS CONSUMED,

575
00:33:53,114 --> 00:33:55,659
APPARENTLY IN ALCOHOL.

576
00:33:55,701 --> 00:33:57,536
PHLOX: SPECIFICALLY, THE TOXIN
WAS BONDED TO A MOLECULE

577
00:33:57,577 --> 00:34:01,206
UNIQUE TO XARANTINE ALE.

578
00:34:02,708 --> 00:34:04,584
THERE WAS A RAID.

579
00:34:04,626 --> 00:34:06,837
ARCHER: YES?

580
00:34:08,672 --> 00:34:11,466
I CAN UNDERSTAND YOUR NOT
WANTING TO TALK ABOUT IT

581
00:34:11,508 --> 00:34:13,844
IF THE RAID WENT BADLY FOR YOU.

582
00:34:13,886 --> 00:34:15,971
THE XARANTINES
ARE NO MATCH FOR US!

583
00:34:16,013 --> 00:34:18,557
WE ATTACKED THEIR OUTPOST
AND TOOK WHAT WE WANTED.

584
00:34:18,598 --> 00:34:21,393
AND THAT INCLUDED
SOME XARANTINE ALE?

585
00:34:23,186 --> 00:34:25,188
DID YOUR WHOLE CREW DRINK IT?

586
00:34:25,230 --> 00:34:28,107
THE TRIUMPH BELONGED TO ALL.

587
00:34:28,149 --> 00:34:30,485
I'LL TAKE THAT AS A YES.

588
00:34:30,527 --> 00:34:35,240
IT WAS THAT ALE
THAT INFECTED YOU, NOT US.

589
00:34:35,281 --> 00:34:36,992
THINK ABOUT IT.

590
00:34:37,034 --> 00:34:40,161
WHEN DID YOUR CREW
START GETTING SICK?

591
00:34:40,203 --> 00:34:42,121
WAS IT RIGHT AFTER THE RAID?

592
00:34:42,163 --> 00:34:46,334
AFTER YOU CELEBRATED
YOUR VICTORY?

593
00:34:46,376 --> 00:34:48,127
THIS IS A TRICK.

594
00:34:48,169 --> 00:34:50,630
ARCHER: IS IT?
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

595
00:34:50,672 --> 00:34:53,425
BETTER OR WORSE
SINCE THE INJECTION?

596
00:34:56,803 --> 00:34:59,681
WE CAN MAKE ENOUGH OF THIS
FOR YOUR ENTIRE CREW

597
00:34:59,723 --> 00:35:03,810
IF IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

598
00:35:03,852 --> 00:35:05,395
[ SIGHS ]

599
00:35:07,856 --> 00:35:11,026
WHAT IF THIS ISN'T A TRICK?

600
00:35:11,068 --> 00:35:14,071
WHAT IF WE'RE TELLING YOU
THE TRUTH?

601
00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:17,657
YOU'D BE LETTING YOUR CREW DIE
A VERY DISHONORABLE DEATH

602
00:35:17,699 --> 00:35:21,202
WHEN YOU COULD HAVE
SAVED THEM.

603
00:35:21,244 --> 00:35:24,081
CAN YOU LIVE WITH THAT?

604
00:35:30,336 --> 00:35:32,130
HOSHI: 1,000 METERS.

605
00:35:32,171 --> 00:35:33,924
2,000.

606
00:35:33,966 --> 00:35:35,634
3,000.

607
00:35:38,053 --> 00:35:41,180
NO EFFECT!
WE'RE STILL SINKING.

608
00:35:41,222 --> 00:35:43,683
THE SHOCK WAVE DISSIPATED
BEFORE IT REACHED US.

609
00:35:43,725 --> 00:35:45,560
REED: WE NEED TO DETONATE ONE
CLOSER NEXT TIME.

610
00:35:45,602 --> 00:35:47,062
[ CREAKING ]

611
00:35:47,104 --> 00:35:48,981
THE SHIP'S HULL IS UNDER
ENOUGH PRESSURE ALREADY.

612
00:35:49,022 --> 00:35:51,108
IF YOU DETONATE
A TORPEDO TOO CLOSE --

613
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:52,525
REED: AND IF I DON'T?

614
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:54,569
WE NEED TO GENERATE
A LARGE ENOUGH SHOCK WAVE

615
00:35:54,611 --> 00:35:56,195
TO PUSH US INTO A HIGHER ORBIT.

616
00:35:56,237 --> 00:36:00,075
TO DO THAT, THE BLAST HAS TO BE
BIG, AND IT HAS TO BE CLOSE.

617
00:36:02,077 --> 00:36:05,330
YOU HEARD THE SUBCOMMANDER.
LOAD TWO THIS TIME.

618
00:36:10,293 --> 00:36:12,671
SENSOR RESOLUTION'S
DROPPING OFF.

619
00:36:12,712 --> 00:36:14,506
THIS WAS YOUR PLAN?

620
00:36:14,547 --> 00:36:15,757
TO GROPE IN THE DARKNESS

621
00:36:15,799 --> 00:36:17,926
AND HOPE TO STUMBLE
ACROSS MY SHIP?

622
00:36:17,968 --> 00:36:20,303
THAT'S HOW WE FOUND IT
THE FIRST TIME.

623
00:36:20,345 --> 00:36:22,263
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

624
00:36:22,305 --> 00:36:23,932
KLINGON: WHAT WAS THAT?

625
00:36:23,974 --> 00:36:26,267
WEAPONS FIRE.

626
00:36:26,309 --> 00:36:27,644
KLINGON: WHERE?

627
00:36:27,686 --> 00:36:32,899
BEARING 297 MARK 261,
DOWN ABOUT TWO KILOMETERS.

628
00:36:32,941 --> 00:36:34,609
REED: DID IT WORK?

629
00:36:34,651 --> 00:36:36,235
HOSHI: WE'VE MOVED UP,
BUT ONLY 200 METERS.

630
00:36:36,277 --> 00:36:37,612
THAT'S ALL?

631
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:40,115
[ ALARM BEEPS ]

632
00:36:40,157 --> 00:36:42,659
A COMPARTMENT JUST COLLAPSED --
DECK THREE, GREEN SECTOR.

633
00:36:42,701 --> 00:36:44,536
THIS WHOLE DAMN SHIP'S
COMING APART.

634
00:36:44,577 --> 00:36:46,245
HOW MANY TORPEDOES
DO WE HAVE LEFT?

635
00:36:46,287 --> 00:36:48,040
HOSHI: SIX.
REED: LOAD TWO MORE.

636
00:36:48,081 --> 00:36:49,666
HOSHI: IT WON'T BE ENOUGH.
REED: LOAD THE WEAPONS.

637
00:36:49,708 --> 00:36:51,209
WE ALREADY TRIED --
IT DIDN'T WORK.

638
00:36:51,250 --> 00:36:53,128
REED: ENSIGN.
T'POL: SHE'S RIGHT.

639
00:36:53,170 --> 00:36:54,880
WE'LL NEVER REACH
A SAFE ALTITUDE

640
00:36:54,921 --> 00:36:57,256
CLIMBING A FEW HUNDRED METERS
AT A TIME.

641
00:36:57,298 --> 00:36:59,300
THE LONGER WE STAND
AROUND ARGUING,

642
00:36:59,342 --> 00:37:00,468
THE MORE GROUND WE LOSE.

643
00:37:00,510 --> 00:37:03,889
FIRE THEM ALL.

644
00:37:03,930 --> 00:37:06,307
WHAT IF WE DETONATED
ALL THE TORPEDOES AT ONCE?

645
00:37:06,349 --> 00:37:09,227
WE MAY GAIN ENOUGH ALTITUDE,

646
00:37:09,268 --> 00:37:11,479
BUT I DOUBT WE'D MAKE IT
IN ONE PIECE.

647
00:37:11,521 --> 00:37:12,731
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU,

648
00:37:12,772 --> 00:37:14,941
BUT I'M WILLING
TO TAKE THE CHANCE.

649
00:37:14,983 --> 00:37:17,861
WE'LL DETONATE AT 800 METERS.

650
00:37:17,903 --> 00:37:20,613
I WAS THINKING MORE LIKE 500.

651
00:37:20,655 --> 00:37:22,365
LOOK, I DIDN'T COME
ALL THIS WAY

652
00:37:22,407 --> 00:37:26,244
TO GET CRUSHED IN THE ATMOSPHERE
OF SOME ANONYMOUS GAS GIANT.

653
00:37:27,579 --> 00:37:30,331
LOADING PORTS ONE THROUGH SIX.

654
00:37:30,373 --> 00:37:32,167
BRACE YOURSELVES.

655
00:37:34,711 --> 00:37:36,880
TORPEDOES ARMED.

656
00:37:39,091 --> 00:37:40,383
UGH!

657
00:37:41,384 --> 00:37:42,594
OH!

658
00:37:42,635 --> 00:37:45,555
KLINGON: WHAT IS IT?

659
00:37:45,597 --> 00:37:47,057
ANOTHER EXPLOSION.

660
00:37:47,099 --> 00:37:50,102
THERE'S A SHOCK WAVE THIS TIME.
HANG ON!

661
00:38:06,659 --> 00:38:09,328
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

662
00:38:09,370 --> 00:38:10,830
T'POL.

663
00:38:10,872 --> 00:38:12,749
Archer: What have you
been shooting at?

664
00:38:12,791 --> 00:38:14,751
WE USED THE SHOCK WAVES
TO GAIN SOME ALTITUDE,

665
00:38:14,793 --> 00:38:16,419
BUT IT'S ONLY TEMPORARY.

666
00:38:16,461 --> 00:38:18,671
WE'LL START SINKING AGAIN
UNLESS WE CAN COME UP WITH A WAY

667
00:38:18,713 --> 00:38:20,298
TO GET THIS SHIP OUT OF HERE.

668
00:38:20,339 --> 00:38:24,219
I BROUGHT SOMEONE WHO SHOULD
BE ABLE TO HELP DO JUST THAT.

669
00:38:24,261 --> 00:38:26,972
WE'RE DOCKING NOW.

670
00:38:27,013 --> 00:38:28,473
[ BEEP ]

671
00:38:38,357 --> 00:38:42,154
I BELIEVE YOU'VE
ALL MET OFFICER BU'KAH.

672
00:38:43,822 --> 00:38:46,407
WHAT'S THE STATUS
OF THEIR ENGINES?

673
00:38:46,449 --> 00:38:47,700
THE KLINGON CREW

674
00:38:47,742 --> 00:38:49,202
MADE MOST OF
THE NECESSARY REPAIRS

675
00:38:49,244 --> 00:38:51,163
BEFORE THEY WERE OVERCOME,

676
00:38:51,204 --> 00:38:53,957
BUT THE PORT FUSION INJECTOR
IS STILL DAMAGED.

677
00:38:53,999 --> 00:38:57,169
I WILL TEND TO MY OWN SHIP.

678
00:38:57,210 --> 00:38:58,628
I DIDN'T BRING YOU DOWN HERE

679
00:38:58,670 --> 00:39:01,173
JUST SO YOU COULD DIE
WITH YOUR SHIPMATES.

680
00:39:01,214 --> 00:39:04,342
MY CREW RISKED THEIR LIVES
TO GET THIS SHIP OUT OF DANGER.

681
00:39:04,383 --> 00:39:08,805
I DON'T INTEND TO LEAVE
UNTIL THE JOB IS FINISHED.

682
00:39:13,226 --> 00:39:16,688
SIR, THERE ARE TWO SHIPS
APPROACHING AT HIGH WARP.

683
00:39:16,729 --> 00:39:18,439
I THINK THEY'RE KLINGON.

684
00:39:18,481 --> 00:39:20,525
ARCHER: HOW LONG TILL
THEY GET HERE?

685
00:39:20,566 --> 00:39:22,485
16 MINUTES.

686
00:39:22,527 --> 00:39:24,070
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

687
00:39:24,112 --> 00:39:26,239
WE'RE BEING HAILED.
IT'S THE CAPTAIN.

688
00:39:26,281 --> 00:39:27,991
ON SCREEN.

689
00:39:28,033 --> 00:39:32,370
<i>THIS IS KLINGON RAPTOR</i> SOMRAW,
<i>HAILING</i> ENTERPRISE.

690
00:39:32,411 --> 00:39:37,083
<i>REQUEST PERMISSION</i>
<i>TO DISEMBARK FOUR PASSENGERS.</i>

691
00:39:39,127 --> 00:39:41,504
WELL, I DON'T SEE WHY NOT.

692
00:39:48,970 --> 00:39:51,014
I KEPT YOUR SEAT WARM FOR YOU.

693
00:39:51,056 --> 00:39:52,431
THANKS.

694
00:39:52,473 --> 00:39:54,309
GET READY
TO BREAK ORBIT, TRAVIS.

695
00:39:54,351 --> 00:39:56,644
I THINK WE'VE HAD ABOUT ENOUGH
OF THIS PLACE.

696
00:39:56,686 --> 00:39:57,854
AYE, CAPTAIN.

697
00:39:57,896 --> 00:39:59,647
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

698
00:39:59,689 --> 00:40:02,567
IT'S THE RAPTOR, SIR.
THEY'RE HAILING US.

699
00:40:02,608 --> 00:40:04,485
TRIP: CALLING TO SAY THANKS?

700
00:40:04,527 --> 00:40:06,738
I DOUBT IT.

701
00:40:06,779 --> 00:40:09,741
PUT IT THROUGH.

702
00:40:09,782 --> 00:40:11,243
ARCHER: WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

703
00:40:11,284 --> 00:40:13,703
<i>PREPARE TO SURRENDER</i>
<i>YOUR VESSEL.</i>

704
00:40:13,745 --> 00:40:15,997
MAYBE YOUR ENGINEER
NEGLECTED TO TELL YOU,

705
00:40:16,039 --> 00:40:18,875
BUT, UH, WE JUST SAVED YOU
AND YOUR CREW.

706
00:40:18,917 --> 00:40:22,420
<i>YOU VIOLATED OUR SHIP,</i>
<i>ACCESSED OUR WEAPONS.</i>

707
00:40:22,461 --> 00:40:25,631
IT WAS EITHER THAT OR STAND BY
AND WATCH YOU GET CRUSHED.

708
00:40:25,673 --> 00:40:27,633
<i>DISRUPTORS!</i>

709
00:40:27,675 --> 00:40:29,844
TRIP: THEY'RE CHARGING WEAPONS.

710
00:40:34,473 --> 00:40:37,852
YOU WOULDN'T LAST 10 SECONDS
IN A BATTLE WITH US.

711
00:40:37,894 --> 00:40:40,230
YOU'VE GOT
MULTIPLE HULL BREACHES,

712
00:40:40,272 --> 00:40:42,274
YOUR SHIELDS ARE DOWN,
AND FROM WHAT I'M TOLD,

713
00:40:42,315 --> 00:40:43,858
YOU'RE FRESH OUT OF TORPEDOES.

714
00:40:43,900 --> 00:40:46,569
IF I WERE YOU, I'D TAKE
WHAT LITTLE HONOR I HAD LEFT

715
00:40:46,611 --> 00:40:49,197
AND GO HOME.

716
00:40:50,949 --> 00:40:53,451
FIRE ONE SHOT,

717
00:40:53,492 --> 00:40:57,414
AND I'LL BLAST YOU RIGHT BACK
TO WHERE WE FOUND YOU.

718
00:40:57,455 --> 00:41:00,750
[<i> GROWLS</i> ]

719
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:04,629
TRAVIS: THEY'RE MOVING OFF.

720
00:41:06,047 --> 00:41:09,217
GET US OUT OF HERE
BEFORE THEIR FRIENDS SHOW UP.

721
00:41:14,639 --> 00:41:17,642
[ SIGHS ]

722
00:41:25,524 --> 00:41:27,360
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

723
00:41:30,155 --> 00:41:32,531
REED: IS SOMEONE GONNA GET THAT?

724
00:41:32,573 --> 00:41:35,534
HOSHI: YOU'RE CLOSER.

725
00:41:35,576 --> 00:41:37,120
[ SIGHS ]

726
00:41:46,296 --> 00:41:47,588
T'POL.

727
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:49,048
Phlox: This is Dr. Phlox.

728
00:41:49,090 --> 00:41:50,716
You'll be happy to know
that you're now free

729
00:41:50,758 --> 00:41:52,718
of any microbes or parasites.

730
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:56,597
Your captivity in decon is over.

731
00:41:56,639 --> 00:41:58,308
REED: ARE YOU SURE, DOCTOR?

732
00:41:58,350 --> 00:42:00,435
WHO KNOWS WHAT WAS LIVING
ON THAT SHIP?

733
00:42:00,477 --> 00:42:03,646
HOSHI: WHAT IF WE
PICKED UP SOMETHING
YOUR SCANS CAN'T DETECT?

734
00:42:03,688 --> 00:42:05,940
Phlox: Well, I'm
quite sure you didn't.

735
00:42:05,982 --> 00:42:07,859
I've run every possible test.

736
00:42:16,201 --> 00:42:18,453
MAYBE YOU SHOULD RUN THEM AGAIN,
DOCTOR.

737
00:42:18,495 --> 00:42:22,581
I BELIEVE I'M DEVELOPING
A SLIGHT...HEADACHE.

738
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:24,876
Phlox: Of course,
if you insist.

739
00:42:24,917 --> 00:42:26,627
I wouldn't want
to miss anything.

740
00:42:26,669 --> 00:42:29,422
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

741
00:42:29,464 --> 00:42:30,882
[ SIGHING ]

742
00:42:34,886 --> 00:42:37,555
REED: THAT SHOULD BUY US AT
LEAST ANOTHER HALF AN HOUR.

743
00:42:37,596 --> 00:42:38,597
[ BOTH CHUCKLING ]

744
00:42:38,639 --> 00:42:41,351
OH, I COULD STAY IN HERE
ALL DAY.

745
00:42:41,393 --> 00:42:43,644
MMM.

746
00:42:43,686 --> 00:42:48,233
REED: WENT TO A SPA
ONCE IN MEXICO.

747
00:42:48,274 --> 00:42:51,903
THE MOST RELAXING
PLACE I'VE EVER BEEN,

748
00:42:51,944 --> 00:42:55,323
BUT IT DOESN'T
COMPARE TO THIS.

749
00:42:55,365 --> 00:42:59,452
OH, IT CERTAINLY FEELS
NICE TO BE CLEAN AGAIN.

750
00:42:59,494 --> 00:43:02,163
T'POL: IT IS PLEASANT.

751
00:43:05,875 --> 00:43:07,877
DO YOU SMELL THAT?

752
00:43:07,919 --> 00:43:10,922
[ SNIFFS ]

753
00:43:10,963 --> 00:43:13,341
I DON'T SMELL ANYTHING.

754
00:43:13,383 --> 00:43:14,675
EXACTLY.

755
00:43:14,717 --> 00:43:17,720
[ CHUCKLING ]
